{
  "texts": [
    "Feature Extraction leverages existing data to create new features that highlight intricate patterns but may introduce computational overhead.",
    "Feature Transformation ensures compatibility across models by standardizing or normalizing data, particularly for heterogeneous client datasets, although sometimes at the cost of the original data interpretability.",
    "Feature Encoding enables categorical data to be numerically represented, preserving relationships but potentially increasing dimensionality.",
    "Finally, feature construction enriches datasets by deriving new features and enhancing predictions, but it poses risks of redundancy and added complexity.",
    "Together, these techniques significantly enhance the accuracy and utility of federated learning models in malicious client detection."
  ]
}